Sentencas: The sluggish oxygen reduction reaction(ORR) in the cathode is hindering the power density of solid oxide fuel cells(SOFCs).
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: Infiltration of catalyst into the cathode of SOFCs is promising to accelerate the ORR However, the degradation associated with the coarsening of the nanocatalyst is intense.
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: To stabilize the catalyst, atomic layer deposition (ALD) is employed to coat a dual electrocatalyst consisting of a superjacent 2 nm CoOx layer and superjacent 3 nm discrete Pt particles into the porous lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM)/yttria-stabilized zirconia(YSZ) cathode.
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: After 504 h of operation at 750 degrees C, the ALD coating resulted in the peak power density enhancement by similar to 200%, while CoOx becomes Mn-enriched (MnCo)O-x nanograins coupling with nano-Pt.
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: The Pt/(MnCo)O-x nanocouplings are uniformly distributed on the YSZ grain surface, triple-phase boundaries, and at LSM/LSM surface grain boundaries.
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes

Sentencas: This study demonstrates an effective approach of stabilizing the minute amount of catalyst for enhancing ORR activity at elevated temperatures.
Titulo: Synergetic Interaction of Additive Dual Nanocatalysts to Accelerate Oxygen Reduction Reaction in Fuel Cell Cathodes
